76561197966328375,Recommended,313630,23608298,"Posted: 16 June, 2016",all,zbest,"5/5 Stars, absolutely would recommend!This is a VR review of the game.Are there flaws with the VR? Yes. Could it have been done better? Yes. That said, this is still the single best experience so far for the HTC Vive I've played, approximately 40 or so games/experiences (Haven't played starseed yet).The Cons:-Movement can be worked on a bit as it's all over the place regarding which implementation your using. This could arguably be a good thing as well, as you have the opportunity for both normal locomotion and teleporting.-Inventory system is extremely weak and a bit frustrating clicking through until you get to the item you want.-You need a beefy PC. I'm running a 8 core extreme i7 and a 980ti and still had to turn down the settings. The resolution scale should be at 150% no matter what or its blurry but the game still looks fantastic. Disable AA as its making the experience worse.-VR controls not intuitive. If I have a torch, I should be able to light a candle by bringing the flame close. Little things like this break immersion but again this wasn't built ground up for VR.Now for the Pros:-Stunning atmosphere. The game feels amazing and I quickly forget where I actually am. The music, the scenery, the sound effects all work seamlessly to create an amazing experience.-Tension. The game is not a horror game, at least not up to where I am, but it has an amazing tension that is building as I play. No jump scares, but definitely a healthy presence of danger and threat. This is amplified by VR and is quite frankly amazing.-Mystery. This game does a brilliant job at showing you there's something going on but not telling you outright. Its a great balance between trying to find clues while exploring as you progress through the game. Many secrets to be found.-One of the biggest and most important pros are that the Devs are vocal in the community. They're on reddit taking feedback and using it to fix many of the issues we're seeing. The most recent update fixed many of these issues immediately.-Content. As far as the content goes, I would say that this game as 2-3 times as much content as the next highest game on the vive(excluding simulators). This is the first real roomscale game that you can take time to enjoy as you're playing through it and exploring. As great as vanishing realms is, this game has much more meat than just 2 hours!All in all, the pros vastly outweigh the cons and this is a game any vive owner should have. It's truly a shame that the work in progress feature they added (VR) caused it to have so many negative reviews when it clearly says its not ready and in an alpha state. Please note that while the VR is not finished and not perfect, this game MORE than deserves your time and money. If this were any other Vive game, the price should be over 100$ based on the content equivalent of similar Vive games, at 20$ this is an absolute STEAL.Please support the developers and write them a good review as this game is exceptional and the few people who cant read that VR is a work in progress, should not tarnish its reputation.5/5 Stars, absolutely would recommend!"
76561197970343237,Recommended,313630,23427735,"Posted: 6 June, 2016",all,Masa,"One of the best, if not the best game to date for the Vive in terms of immersion.  Worth every penny and a must have if you have a Vive."
,Recommended,313630,30708422,Posted: 24 March,all,Berta,"The Solus Project - detailed reviewThe Solus Projectis an adventure-type game, in which you have to survive on a human-unfriendly planet, where meteor rains and deadly tornadoes are common aspects of living. Your task is to communicate with the mother-ship, however the communication system is broken. As you try to fix it, it turns out that you aren't the first human-like creature to live on that planet.Gameplay conceptThe game puts emphasis on storytelling and atmosphere. As developers mentioned, the game also consists of exploration and survival, but don't take these as major elements. Survival itself isn't demanding and you are guided where to go in order to continue. Unless you want to explore deeper, optional areas - to find out every secret hidden in the game - you won't have any problems.ProsMusicBeautiful, ambient music composed by Jonas Kjellberg accompanies you through the entire journey. It changes depending on where you are, what you are doing and whether you are in danger or not. I have to admit that without so magnificent music this game would be much worse experience.StoryRich in secrets, complex environment pays off for rather linear story with no side quests. There are plenty of references to famous alien-like movies, books, etc., but I won't mention them here (find them!). Story idea itself is quite genuine and well told. It also does contain some horror-like elements, which, together with magnificent music mentioned above, creep you out very well. Great!Graphics & visual performanceCongratulations to developers! Smoothly rendered and good quality graphics are hard to achieve, but here it couldn't have been done better. I haven't experienced any lag issues so far and had all the chunks loaded before entering a certain location - perfect!ConsPoor fauna/floraWhile locations like alien structures or caves are really detailed and diverse, flora and fauna could be much more improved. It simply lacks variety, even for the planet with surface created of rocks. Why not add bird-like creatures, if we already can hear them in the game, some fish living in the ocean or stone-like plants chilling at the beach - huge field to fill the game with details, yet not used for anything.SurvivalUnlimited torch fire. Unlimited water source in every cave. Unlimited food and water every checkpoint. Multiple full food/water recovery snacks found everywhere. Plenty of rockets filled with resources dropping from mother-ship. Come on guys, how is it survival? Even while exploring some deeper areas never was I even close to dying from thirst or hunger. And that's almost the harderst difficulty level. In addtion, nearly all puzzles could be solved in seconds and multiple traps found both in caves and alien buildings definitely couldn't be described as ""deadly”. I actually used the fire ones to warm myself in cold areas. Smart, isn't it?OverallTo conclude, The Solus project is a beautiful, astonishing game. Its main strengths are story and atmosphere, yet it lacks diversity in planet nature and survival aspects. I strongly recommend it to every adventure seeking person!Score: 7.5/10"
