,Recommended,313630,26479963,"Posted: 7 November, 2016",all,STURM-KATTEN [SC-KL],"This is a really impressive story game that presents you elements of survival, exploration and treasure-hunting.I really liked it, especially buying it at half price, I thought it was excellent value for money - at the sale price only. My reason for this is because it is a one-play linear game. As soon as I had completed it, my enjoyment there ended. Reading the text within the game, (the notes left by people there, or signs carved into walls etc), played a part in my enjoyment-for-money, so I recommend reading what you can, but it is not essential. I even made my own alphabet and was able to decypher the alien language, it really is accurate! (I even found a translation mistake on one of the slabs of text, but I was able to translate what it said myself, so that was rather fun in itself lol!)Even though the fun is over now for me, I will say that the game most likely requires a re-play because there are some very well-hidden secrets to be found! I would replay it for the completion factor I think.These secret treasures combine to 'upgrade' your survivability stats and are banked as soon as you obtain them. I would only replay the game to find all secrets for the completion factor, not for the upgrades, since I enjoyed the difficulty and challenge of the survival element. Oh and if you are a hard-case, you can make it hard, so don't worry about collecting the secret treasures.It pays to keep paying attention to your vital stats, featured on your hand-held device. You need to do whatever you need to to survive and that involves preventing numerous ways that you can die from happening. So make sure you box - clever. With this in mind, I will give you some helpful advice about what you are likely to encounter in the game;1) At the start of each area/level, you will encounter small 'worship shrines', 6 ft high pointed stones, standing in the ground (that are actually spelled 'woship' lol, but hey never mind). What these are telling you is how many artifacts, secret treasures, are to be found in that area/level, which is neat because that will be useful for the second play-through.2) Secondly, you will come across 'Cargo Manifest' crates, that list certain items of use, but the cargo box appears to be empty. What are they? Well, these are telling you what special items are to be found in that given area/level - much like the shrines that tell you about the hidden artifacts! (I had to google to find this out, since I found it confusing and didn't get it). This did not ruin the game, since I enjoy having to find things out for myself and not have my game played for me or my hand held. However, it may as well be given as advice to save time for those who just want to get on with the game.As you adventure along in this Alien world you come across different items that you can decide for yourself if you want them or not and yes.. there is no 'right or wrong'. You only need food, water and sleep to survive, so your inventory is yours for the making. I liked that.However, I'm not sure why some objects were there in the game, what role they actually played because for me, I didn't find much use for them. Nevertheless, this did not spoil the game at all for me, I enjoyed unravelling the mystery cave by cave, engraving by engraving and with every turning of a key, which unlocked more of the game as I played.I do recommend this game, as long as you don't mind not having any guns. Still.. you can always make a Hammer.."
