76561198075525997,Recommended,313630,21558610,"Posted: 29 February, 2016",all,budwheizzah,"The Solus Project forces my hand into giving a positive review for three simple reasons:1) Developer communication. Having had fairly important issues initially running this game in virtual reality (Oculus DK2) I had to resort to the community hub for some help, which finally ame in the form of an update from the developers. Not only were my issues resolved, but options were added to resolve issues others were having, and in the end we even got options that are a welcome extra. Devs that communicate so openly and then deliver on the discussion need to be recognized.2) Amazing performance. While the game is in ""late early access"", the VR portion of it is far less complete, but what makes it easy to handle - not being the case with most VR games - is the butter-smooth performance. When I'm not using any recording software I've seen the game stick at 75fps without even touching any of the stock settings. This will lgo a long way in making your playthrough smoother.3) Well polished. This part applies less to VR and more to the game overall... for what is being delivered, the game is almost there. They seem to have their mechanics about 95% the way, and at this point most of what's not here yet is actual content.The game has gotten my attention enough to select it for a let's play video series.Here's the DailyMotion 2D-only version of my first impressions video:http://www.dailymotion.com/video/x3uzrpz_oculus-rift-dk2-the-solus-project_tech"
