76561198058359314,Recommended,313630,33889608,Posted: 29 July,all,ecke,"Personal rating: 6 out of 10This game left me quite confused by the end. I am sure that i's worth the time (hence I am still recommending it), but one should be willing to deal with a very MIXED experience.The game carries REALLY GREAT potential, mainly in terms of atmosphere. The overall mood really took my breath, at least during the first ours of gameplay! The most beautiful parts were, in my opinion:1.) the DYNAMIC BACKGROUND music, which makes for an extremely thrilling experience.2.) The underworld, which has some very strong resemblances to Skyrim's dwemer ruins. However, they're even better than them! I found myself thinking over and over again: ""This is how dungeons in Elder Scrolls SHOULD HAVE been"". So, chapeau for that!On the other hand, the game seems to ""gamble away"" its potential continously during the plot, due to at least THREE MAJOR WEAKNESSES:1.) The general idea of surviving an escalating threat in a mysterious unknown environment is nice, but waaaaaay too long drawn-out. You find yourself stumbling through a ridiculously long serious of sequential chapters (geographically represented by separated isles and underworld sections), but without any major change in gameplay mechanisms, and also without a real ""open world"" feeling - the latter being suggested by the game, of course, but not really fulfilled (most of the sideways don't bear significant secrets or surprises - just follow the given narrative and walking path, that's it) - so it simply grows tiring over time. The attempt to produce a climax in storytelling simply doesn't work.2.) There are some obvious, but very nasty BUGS.The worst part (which happened to me, like to many others, as a quick google search revealed) is that you may end up right before the ending (completing the tower), only to recognize that the game has lost the proper status of your game (i.e. tower parts suddenly missing, though I had already installed them). I had to apply excessive console tweaking just to be able to experience the ending.3.) The ending itself.It is up to personal taste, of course. But I've seen better. I myself found it very disappointing, and above all: too straight and PREDICTABLE. Don't wanna spoil here, but I had expected something really more interesting than a flat, horror-style ""doom end"" that explains nothing at all.SUMMARY:I have high respect for the major IDEA of this game, and the CREATIVITY that has been put into at least some aspects of it, but it lacks consistency and a true arc of suspense. It seems to be an uncomplete piece of work by gifted creators.A GREAT idea, but unfortunately, only partially accomplished.So I hope that its creators will keep up their good work and show us that they can do better!"
