76561198028580195,Recommended,313630,23473921,"Posted: 9 June, 2016",all,Chaaan,"I played this on PC. The game runs pretty well at 1080p. I only got noticeable frame rate drops when there were a lot of overlapping dynamic lights. This is my setup:Intel i5-2500k Sandy Bridge processor8 GB of RAMNVIDIA GTX 770Pros:- The planet's moon affects the tides, causing some areas to become easily accessible or difficult to access, respectively. This combined with the different weather effects makes outside world feels very dynamic and gives the sense that you are truly at nature's will.- The environments and effects are done really well. There is enough visual and aural feedback to give you a sense of your environment. For example, during the day the sun is so hot that you will begin to suffer heatstroke if you exposed for too long. Heat shimmer will begin to appear on the horizon as a visual cue that you shouldn't stay exposed for too long. Likewise, frost will form on the terrain when it is very cold.Cons:- Character movement feels a bit clunky. Character movement acceleration is so low that it takes a while to ""ramp up"" to full walking speed. This causes your movement to feel a bit unresponsive and sluggish.- You only feel like you're playing a true survival game for a few portions of the game. After a while, the survival aspect kind of takes a step back and the game becomes a full on adventure/exploration/puzzle game, with the survival kind of nagging you on the side. This is largely due to the fact that there are pots of alien soup and pools of drinkable water scattered throughout the game. Eventually the need to manage your inventory and plan ahead goes away completely.- Many of the environments, especially the caves and interiors, start to feel very same-y after a while.Pro tips:- Crouching and then jumping allows you to ""spring up"" and get a higher jump.- The teleport gun is very useful for traversing the map. You can combine that with jumping to launch the disc farther. You can use it to wander out for supplies and quickly recall back to home base. You can use it to escape bad situations."
