76561198119163670,Recommended,313630,23509877,"Posted: 11 June, 2016",all,burningupasun,"I originally bought this game when it was in Beta, though not from the very start. I love a good walking/exploration tye game, and I enjoy SciFi, so this seemed like it would be great... and it was! It reminded me of one of my first video games loves, Myst, only much more intense and a bit creepier. I had a ton of fun exploring each section of the planet, finding all the little secrets and unfurling the story. I loved it so much that when I hit my first end-point, rather than wait for the game to be updated, I went and played it again from the start on a harder level (and with a focus towards getting all the secrets too). It was even better the second time around, and with each update, and I really loved how the deeper into the game I went, the more and more creepy it became. There were quite a few moments where I was playing too late at night and got very creeped out!So all in all, this is a really wonderful game, especially if you want something you can enjoy over a long period of time rather than just rushing right through. It's a slow game, but perfectly paced for those who like exploration and a nice slow build. I loved the story itself of course (although I did see the end coming, but that was still okay, it didn't ruin it for me), I enjoyed all the puzzles (and having to solve them without any help since this game is so relatively new!), and on top of that I also really loved the game graphic and design. It felt like I was right there on this mysterious alien world-- I can only imagine how that would feel if I owned a VR device! I even enjoyed the survival aspects even if they're probably what I am the worst at. (Actually what I'm the worst at is falling off ledges in this game and hurting/near-killing myself, whoops!)Anyway to sum up, I highly, highly recommend this to anyone who likes scifi, puzzles, exploration, and a hint of a creepy factor! Enjoy!!"
