76561198085555647,Not Recommended,313630,28672416,"Posted: 26 December, 2016",all,King Haggis,"Sluggish, slow, boring, overhyped and VERY buggy. Not even remotely fun. Especially annoying when savegames stop working or when you have to keep trying to work around the various bugs in the graphical interface and menu's. Not much freedom to explore at all. The ""big"" islands only let you walk along a fixed path and survival ingredients are always very conviently present at the right time when you need them most. Predictable as hell. This whole game is scripted and not dynamic.Gameplay is mostly about letting you walk around a room, a cave or small outdoor sector to solve a puzzle and trying to make the world look bigger than it actually is by making you have to walk from one corner of the sector to the other and back again to push buttons and levers and collect necessary items. This is not a big world, simply a lot of small sectors stitched together combined with a slow walking speed.The story and atmosphere are kind of okay but nothing to write home about either. I get the feeling this is supposed to be more like an ""experience"" than a game. The VR with an Oculus Rift is decent and very much recommended because I can't imagine me playing this game longer than 60 minutes if I didn't have a Rift. Even if you do like this game, it's probably a one time experience at best. It has very limited replayability as it's just a scripted story.To sum it up, the game just fails at almost everything it tries to achieve:Puzzles are too boring and easy and just included to keep the total gametime artificially long, action is non existent, story is nothing special, survival is a joke, the ""big world"" is a small world. Graphics are bland but okay, music is absent, sound is okay, game is buggy.I really wished this was more like the old Unreal game and then with a bigger procedurally generated world and with survival aspects. Unreal had good graphics, fast paced action, nice puzzles, an awesome atmosphere, fast pace story telling and very good music. Guess I was wrong about this one and fell for the hype surrounding it. It could have been a winner but I'll never play it again. Maybe nice for patient people with a lot of imagination but even those would have to agree it's not more to them than a 6 out of 10 as there are far better games than this one in the ""puzzle genre"".For anyone else, it's probably a 3 out of 10. Nice try, but no cigar."
