76561198061256825,Not Recommended,313630,28645099,"Posted: 25 December, 2016",all,wassupwiyou,"As played on a high rig PC.A pity this game's interface is such rubbish because it had the makings of something good, special even. But the muddled procedure you have to go through to combine items and 'craft' them is terrible. It took a while before I found I had to discard items and then find a different item from the inventory to modify the discarded one. So if you want to eat canned food you find a tin, discard it, perform clicks to open the can with a sharp rock, then pick up said can again and click to eat the content. Clumsy, barmy, inane. Whoever concocted this convoluted method must have had common sense lessons from a confused monkey that fell out of a tree while trying to learn the alphabet backwards.Graphically the game is pretty good and the scenario is sound enough, only in my view the implementation is awful. The inventory system needs an overhaul (well, trashing actually). Why not have a designated key for eating and drinking from items possessed, if not text options to click on? Simple. This is so basic and fundamental it's quite amazing how some folk like to complicate the mechanics of the simplest of tasks as if eating and drinking is a challenging riddle in itself. Despair.At the outset you have to exit from a small area. However, I decided jumping was the most logical means but there was an artifical barrier that stopped me from simply dropping a couple of feet over to the other side. Hmm, bad start, I thought and wasn't proved wrong. After wandering around the beaches for hours searching for numerous parts to build a comms rig I became tired of eating , drinking, being advised my suit was wet, etc etc, and decided to see 1/ How far I could scale the cliffs, and 2/ If I could swim to the other islands not too far out to sea. I managed to scale the cliffs with some effort while logically thinking that there must be ship debris up there to collect. But no, nothing whatsover despite the wreckage strewn on the beaches  below. An opportunity missed surely. Regarding swimming to the other islands, you can't because you hit an invisible barrier halfway there.Is this really open world? Well, yes, but in a restrictive sort of way. I think this game needs to be thought out more. For starters ditch the clumsy inventory interface and the continual reminders you're wet, thirsty, hungry, etc. Yawn... If this is a survival game let's have options to turn off the hand-holding. On that note I am personally sick of the Simple Simon approach to most game designs these days as if evey player has an IQ lower than a gorilla with dementia.The game promised a lot but there needs to be more freedom and intelligent structure. It needs a better user experience even at budget price. Work in progress I guess but 8/10 for effort and visuals."
