,Recommended,313630,24411475,"Posted: 19 July, 2016",all,MackDaddy,"This is currently one of my favorite VR games. I know originally it wasn't designed for VR, but it does it quite well. There has been a few times where I just sit down on the beach in awe and stare at how beautiful the sky is.  I have not finished this game yet, and that is a great thing. Most VR experiences are short. This is a long play through, it has some puzzle elements. Some people say this is a walking simulator. That’s fine with me; it sure is a hell of a one. I sometime feel like I’m on an episode of Star Trek, or in the Aliens movie.While they continue to improve on the VR controls, my only complaint is the horrible inventory selection system. Having to click through each item is not fun, and when you miss it, you have to go around the bend/wheel again. Not a big deal in the beginning, but when you get further in and have collected a lot more stuff, it gets frustrating.  I really enjoy the atmosphere, and there are some chilling moments to be hand in the game."
76561197978083422,Recommended,313630,23522757,"Posted: 12 June, 2016",all,Daemonfall,"I have to say that I really enjoyed this game. The gameplay is well-balanced and the difficulty level is completely customizable.I really thought that the survival mechanics paired with the planet's weather patterns made for a rich and rewarding experience. Also while not on the surface, a somewhat maze-like puzzle experience awaits you (no complex puzzles though, you mostly just wander through the maze and challenging environment to find switches).There are a large number of secrets in this game to add extra challenge/exploration/rewards if you wish, but they are optional.The story is left to discovery by the player. There are fragments of notes and such left throughout the levels, and the story is somewhat left to personal interpretation.There are no ""fights"" to speak of, but there are occasions where you may need to stealth past or run past certain ""enemies"". The times when you are trying to escape an anomaly are well-done and appropriately intense, but these are interspersed between periods of less-intense play so as to not give you PTSD.TL;DR: A great sci-fi adventure-survival game, well worth the price I paid of $20 USD. Not intense but not boring either; a well-balanced and thought-provoking challenge in the genre."
