,Recommended,313630,28390414,"Posted: 15 December, 2016",all,Jearbear,"Ever wonder what it would be like to survive a spaceship crash and embark on a Giorgio A. Tsoukalos mystery investigation? Well look no further than the Solus Project. This fairly lengthly narrative driven surival game takes the normally (to me at least) dull eat food, drink water, don't freeze to death mechanics of a surive in the woods game and combines them with a puzzle exploration openish? world of neat rocks n' things.To me this game was well worth it's not too steep price, and was definitely something I would consider an enjoyable experience, despite the game itself not having much going for it other than a spectacular atmosphere. Even knowing that 90% of the time I was completely safe, as stated in the description there's no real enemies, the atmosphere created such a wonderful feeling of anxiety and nigh terror that I would still tense at every random background ambience noise.A solid game, worth picking up if you just want a chill game to play looking at some neat things. The only drawbacks are that the game is fairly easy, even the survival elements are most of the time fairly trivial unless you drop all your food and forget to pick it back up (which I only did once) as there's a pretty consistently spaced supply of unlimited food and water. So don't pick this up if you are looking for a challenge, but otherwise I'd recommend it.Overall rating: 8/10"
