,Recommended,313630,25790667,"Posted: 30 September, 2016",all,tdc,"The Solus Project is an atmospheric exploration and puzzle solving survival game. It's package provides both VR-enabled and normal gameplay experience.The sole survivor of an event whereby your spacecraft was destroyed, you awake on an alien world. It's up to you to work out the whys and wherefores as you explore your seemingly uninhabited surroundings. Collecting resources, making tools, gathering food...all of this and more is required to keep you upright and breathing. Occasionally an overhead relay satelite will align with your communication device and for all too brief moments you'll be able to hear your mothership trying to contact you. Unfortunately your personal communicator lacks the power to answer...Technically TSP is an Unreal Engine game. On my, admittedly beastly, PC it runs with no graphical issues at 4K although levels take a noticably long time to load. Not too sure what that's about but once loaded all is fine.I personally enjoy playing the game. There is some handholding regarding where to go and what to do, but certainly nothing of the sort when it comes to working out or solving the puzzles. The story is interesting, the world is huge and the environments, levels if you will, are clearly lovingly designed. I give it 7.5/10."
