el longer distances in a faster way (eg. if you wanna go back to already explored areas you have to travel back by walking which sometimes can take hours.. )The story is ok but honestly to me it wasn't the story who made me love this game, it is just the way everything is balanced out in this world. The interaction of the weather climate change, rain, snow, day night cycles, caves and how it affects your body temeperature etc. just feels on spot. The soundtrack is good (complements the game really well) and adds more drama to the situation. The World, sky at day&night looks stunningly gorgeous and gives you totally the feel that you really are there on this planet, a very immersive game! Just the look of the game made me wanna explore more of this beautiful world. I truly felt like an exploring new worlds pioneer. :)This is definitly a must-have for every space explorer pioneer, sci-fi and survival lovers out there! If you're looking for killing and shooting stuff, aliens etc. this might not be the game for you. If you're a curious, patient gamer and are into adventure/exploring/survival-games and if you like to got immersed and find out more of what's going on on this Planet, just give this a try. Overall price/package conclusion = TOP!! To me definitly best indie game of the year, please more of this!!(sorry for my english it's not my native language..)"
