,Recommended,313630,24084841,"Posted: 4 July, 2016",all,FunBotan,"Pros:- The survival part is BOTH logical AND fun at the same time! There are just enough items to create a diversity of survival strategies while not creating a mess in your inventory and memory. Scavenging for resourses is more like entertainment than a job-that-needs-doing and it doesn't take much time on average even at hard difficulty. Hiding from a tornado under thin shipwreck while freezing to death has never been that fun, or at least I've never seen it done better.- Level design. The mandatory routes are pretty damn convinient, but the deeper you dig, the more realistic your environment becomes. There are actually multiple layers of secret passages stretching for miles away.- Physics. With the exception of thermodynamics-defying Alien Technology™, but who cares.- Unexpected plot twists made to scare the s*** out of you, Indiana Jones style.Cons:- The story. Sometimes it almost feels like there is one, but...- Too easy! It's a shame for such a content-rich game to be completeable in under 12 hours.tl;dr: Recommended for those who prefer to stray from the scripted path and explore the world."
