76561197960326925,Recommended,313630,23614935,"Posted: 17 June, 2016",all,Neural,"This is a review for the VR version of the game.  I'm playing in the Vive.The VR component of the game really should be beta or Early Access.  The flat monitor version apparently is much less rough around the edges.  That being said, if you have a Vive...BUY THIS GAME!  The atmosphere in this game is AMAZING.  I really felt that I was exploring an alien world!  It's difficult to articulate exactly how profound this is if you haven't tried the Vive, but for that experience alone, it was well worth the price.  This is what I'm basing my recommendation on.  Any warts the game has don't matter to me because I was actually exploring an alien world in VR!  Thank you!  This is what I bought into VR for!  To explore new worlds!I never played the initial version of the game that had locomotion and other VR-related issues, I played the one after that which allowed for teleport locomotion and/or head tracked touch pad movement.  I like this solution and I think it works great.  You can tell this is not a 'made-for-VR' game but rather a port because at this writing, you can break some puzzles by just walking through walls.  Games like The Gallery and Vanishing Realms handle this by blurring your vision or teleporting you back to the playing field.   This game doesn't do that yet.The inventory system is acknowledged by the developers as inadequate and there is a new system being implemented this weekend, I read.  However, it's servicable as is.  I'm looking forward to their improving it, but I've a few hours and it's a bit tedious, but works.The crafting system and PDA are a bit confusing to use in VR, especially if you're used to other games like Vanishing Realms or The Gallery.  Again, you can tell this was made for a gamepad or mouse/kb and not VR.  Once you figure it out, it's fine.  It works.  I wish the interactions were more intuitive.  I wish I could take my torch and place the flame over a candle to light the candle instead of holding the torch, highlighting the candle with my pointer and ""using"" the torch on the candle.  It's a bit awkward.I'm really excited to see how the developers continue to improve The Solus Project for VR and I'm very encouraged by their progress so far!"
