76561198011328167,Recommended,313630,23881337,"Posted: 27 June, 2016",all,Gizmodian,"TLDR: This game is amazing.I am playing without VR, as a regular first person shooter style. In the dark, with only myself and my glowing monitor even vaguely visible.My first moments in the game was inspiring. I had no idea what I was doing, the world felt harsh and hostile and I was in awe of the sheer scale.I felt lost. Alone.It was perfect.The sound and ambience sucks you in. Audio cues tell you what's going on. I highly suggest headphones, surround sound if you've got 'em.The handcrafted nature of the world is obvious. Beautiful landscapes. Contoured caves. Convoluted secrets.The world itself is your enemy. Heat. Cold. Starvation.Storms.  The storms themselves are a sight to behold of terrifying proportions.Any of these can kill the careless and unprepared.Though the game itself is not particularly brutalizing and there are several levels of difficulty in which to choose from.  I played on balanced, and it was just that. Balanced well.  You don't grind to survive.  You scavenge and prepare and make decisions.I actually made a terrible decision at one point in the game, losing my torch. I battled constantly threatening hypothermia, but with a little tact, I managed to make it past the area.  Even if you make a mistake, not all is lost.Be smart when playing, and it's not a frustrating adventure in finding out how angry a game can make you.  It will take you on a fantastic story driven adventure.The only small issue I find with the game is that it's incredibly difficult to backtrack. The cave systems are winding mazes, and if you're an idiot like me and don't get all the tower pieces in each area, you're going to have a bad time.Because of this, I have not yet finished the ending, but the journey so far has been easily worth what I paid for the game."
