76561197970833892,Recommended,313630,24193389,"Posted: 8 July, 2016",all,MooTheCow,"I played this in VR and even though VR-mode is currently only in Beta, I found the experience amazing and enthraling.  Would totally recommend it.The sense of presence in some of the areas (particularly the caves) is huge.  And when various monsters appear (which happens only after a few hours of peaceful exploration) then they have a real sense of danger.  Particularly when you are waiting in the dark listening to a monster passing, and afraid to equip your torch for fear it sees it.  And yet there aren't really any jump-scares, just occassional areas which give a sense of dread.  This is an exploration game, not a horror game.--Edit to my original review to state that the VR inventory has been updated and now works great.  And this, combined with the dev's visible work in this area, means that I am confident that the remaining VR issues (which are not so annoying as to detract from the whole marvelous experience) will be ironed out.  I don't want niggling mention of small issues to mar this review and potentially put people off a purchase, so I've removed them from the review and into their proper place as a bug report.So much have I enjoyed Solus that on upgrading from my 770 GTX (which actually ran the game fine on lower settings) to a new 1070 GTX, that I started my 10 hour campain again from scratch in all its graphical quality!"
,Recommended,313630,24231817,"Posted: 10 July, 2016",all,Maffi,"This game is amazing! The ""story"", if you want to call it that, is good. It is literally exploration, and only what you seek out and find, that makes the story.What i am trying to say is, you can basically run through the game and not read anything or pay minimal attention to the things around you, but why would you do this?But now a few other, minor things that should be mentioned, for example the performance.It uses the Unreal Engine but sometimes stutters really bad, that has to do with the sky and ocean reflection updates.If you receive these kind of stutters, then there is a fairly easy fix for it:go and open:steamapps\common\TheSolusProject\Solus\Config\DefaultGame.iniin the config find and change following from True to False:AllowOceanUpdate=FalseAllowSkylightUpdate=FalseThis will help a lot, also go and enable FXAA in your driver settings, if you are on an nvidia card, this did help tremendously with my frames per second, boosting it from 45-50 to 90-95fps.TL;DR: Good game for little money for all explorers and spelunkers that know how to basic computer"
