,Recommended,313630,28660680,"Posted: 25 December, 2016",all,Technus,"I really enjoyed this game and played most of it in VR.  Here are the things I like about it:1. Tornadoes - The tornadoes are scary and the music that comes with them make them even more terrifying.2. Nice graphics and great sound effects and music.   I loved the cave with all the giant, glowing mushrooms.  I also loved the giant moon, that was my favorite scene.3.  First person and very immersive.4.  Very Interesting story line.  The further you get into the game, the more you learn about the alien race that used to inhabit the planet and what happened to them.Tips on playing:1. When in doubt, use your teleporter.  It serves as more than just for teleporting you back to a cave when the weather gets bad.2. Food is everywhere, you don't have to stock up on it too much.3. Don't swim with your torch ;)**Warning Spoilers below**Suggestions for improvement (I know the game is no longer early access, but I think these would have made the game even better):1. There should be a suggestion in the beginning to use your teleporter to get into the first cave.  I was completely clueless on this and didn't think I could shoot it in there for some reason.  I actually stopped playing for quite some time because I got stuck on this and couldn't find the solution.2.  The player seems to care less about the aliens he actually encounters.  For example, when you get to the top of the windmill and activate it and then make a log afterwards, he says absolutely nothing about the reptilian/predator looking entity that was chained up trying to literally bite your head off.  I think that would have been important to note because it is the first alien contact you have.  That was not the only instance.  He reported once that he ""thought"" he saw one when in fact it was standing right in front of you.  Unless you really weren't paying attention, it's impossible to miss.  That probably should have been said the first time you saw one for the very first time standing in a window (which he said nothing about!).3.  I know VR is ""expiremental"" but there was some shimmering lights around plants and some other things that threw off the feel and graphics a bit.4. There should be more than just the 15 components around the islands.  I thought I got them all but was left 1 short.  I tried my best to retrace my steps, which took forever! but was not able to find that last one.  Had to use a cheat command.  Also, not everyone thoroughly searches everything, which is why there should be an abundance of the parts.5. There should be manual save options so I can go back to an older save.  I ran into a couple issues and was not able to load an older file so had to use cheat commands (like the time a pillar got stuck up on a ledge somehow)."
