,Not Recommended,313630,26366844,"Posted: 1 November, 2016",all,Unforseen Liquid Emission,"Disclaimer:  I played this on PC (non VR)This game doesn't seem to know what it wants to be.On one hand, it's an exploration / adventure game,  which makes sense seeing as it is the spiritual sequel to ""The Ball"" which had a heavy emphasis on puzzles and adventure, with nary a survival element to be found. Unfortunately it seems as though Sjoerd realized that it was 2016 , and survival games were popular, so he shoe-horned in a bunch of ill-fitting survival mechanics which do very little to make the game enjoyable.  I'd go as far as to say that they shoot it in the foot.Swimming will make your character cold and wet, and quickly kill you from hypothermia.  Not that there's much to see underwater anyway, it's mostly just an empty expanse of sand.  Your character will constantly complain about needing food, so you will be forced to bash open tin cans with rocks and repetetively munch on the contents until the suit stops ♥♥♥♥♥ing at you.  There are text logs scattered throughout the world which you can discover with your ""WILSON"" (LOL Castaway reference!) device.  They aren't very interesting.They say first impressions are everything,  and this game doesn't make a very good one. It is fairly mediocre looking with low poly assets and low resolution textures.  It somewhat compensates for this with a stylized look that was also present in ""The Ball"" (textures tend to look hand painted), but the best I could say about it is that it looks passable.  Kind of like a better than average looking Unreal Engine 3 game ( Bulletstorm came to mind in spots)  Given that it needs to run at a high framerate to support VR devices, this isn't a huge surprise.  Don't expect your jaw to be dropping to the floor here.Fairly dissappointed in this one.   It was developed by an indie dev I respect, and I *want* to like it, but It's just not grabbing me.  Maybe I'll give it another try another time, but for now, I'd recommend that if you want an exploration / survival game that is actually decent try Subnautica or The Long Dark instead."
