76561198085061200,Recommended,313630,21323338,"Posted: 19 February, 2016",all,t3opc,"Starts off with a nice story line. You begin on an alien planet and need to survive by gathering supplies into your backpack and/or gathering them in a cave.The nights are very cold and the days are warm, so at night you need to keep warm. You do this by finding the necessary supplies then using them to stay safe. Once you do so, you can begin to explore more safely.There are puzzles, traps, secrets, and more along the way. Backstory is provided via pages strewn around from the wreakage. Some story is also provided by alien structures/monuments. The rest of the story is provided by voice.The sound effects and music are all really good and help pull you into it.As this review is from Early Access, there's currently some bugs. Nothing major.But, some annoying things could be better such as when getting wet its quite difficult to read the in-game UI as there's these big water droplets in the way that may not be moving out of the way.The water droplet animation is REALLY bad.And some other things... what they improve or fix in the end just isn't known at this time.You can jump and move around at will. Into the water you go! The ONLY invisible walls I've noticed are deep at sea.There's plenty more to find out for yourself...Overall, definitely recommended. I haven't wanted to play a survival based game until now. This one is good.(Its best to have a short review for this game as the more you read the more its going to take away from the discovery aspect of it which is very important here.)"
